<br>
She was wrapped in a soft white cloth to symbolize the purity of her future marriage and the love bound within it. <br>
<br>
One of the Shamaness' spoke: &quot;Any of the Amazon Nation may at this time participate in the cleansing of the Queen's Body, Mind, Heart and Soul. No pain shall come to her for she has endured what has been asked of her already.&quot; She smiled lightly. &quot;She shall have peace brought into her soul and blessings upon her from us all.&quot; <br>
<br>
Every Guest inside the hut was given a small white stone. <br>
<br>
&quot;You have been given stones of purity to ensure the cleansing nature of this ritual. Please drop them all into the hot spring one at a time. You may say your blessings of good nature to the queen and her marriage as you do this.&quot; She motioned her hand to a small hotspring that the sweat hut had been built around.<br>
<br>
Alysia lay there as a few of the Shamaness' lit candles and inscence around her. Some then began rubbing oils and sea salts into her feet and hands.<br>
<br>
Alysia had been asked to remain silent through this sacred ritual. And she would do so.<br>
